This paper discusses a technique for secure in-process isolation, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also mentions the use of memory protection keys (MPKs), which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the technique in nginx, a web server, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
